{ A c5 break is an important idea in many openings as Black since it provides counterplay and frees Black's pieces. The risk in any unbalanced position is that it becomes sharper. That means that its easier to win or lose the game in just one move because tactics are more prevalent. As a result we need to be ready to respond to several moves for White here if we are going to be tournament ready. }
2. Nf3
{ You are sitting at the board and your opponent plays Nf3 here. Ask yourself, is the position unbalanced yet? What is my immediate plan? Answer those questions and Black's next move should make sense based on what you have learned so far. }
2... Nf6
{ Yes the position is imbalanced, and the plan is to get castled and get developed. Bam that makes Nf6 the natural move based on our previous lines. }
3. O-O c4
