7. h3 { preventing Bg4 } 7... h6
{ Preventing Bg5. Now you have a position where you can comfortably play against the isolated pawn. Without going into too much detail here on how to play against isolated pawns. Trading minors is often good, control the d5 square in front of the pawn, and in the long term try to win the d pawn without letting white get a big attack.    While it may seem easy, these transpositions are important to know and recognize for a complete tournament repertoire. }
