Qe7+
{ This can feel unatural since we have played our knight to e7 in several lines. However with the queen on f3 the white knight is going to e2, so we want our knight on f6. }
3. Ne2 Nc6
{ Pressuring the d-pawn which is only guarded by the knight on e2. The knight on e2 is already a bit overloaded guarding the d4 pawn and the other knight on c3. }
